Array Properties in Java
1. ✅ Fixed Size
Once an array is created, its size cannot be changed.

2. ✅ Indexed Access
Array elements are accessed using indexes starting from 0.

3. ✅ Same Data Type
All elements in the array must be of the same type.

4. ✅ Stored in Contiguous Memory
Arrays are stored in continuous memory locations, so they allow fast access.

5. ✅ Default Values
If you create an array and don’t assign values, Java gives default values:

6. ✅ .length Property
To get the size of array (number of elements):

7. ✅ Arrays are Objects in Java
Arrays are actually objects, so you can use them with loops and methods.

